To make SEDutil USB 
  Got to--> https://sedutil.com/ 
  then download 
  Transfer Rescue image to the USB stick with a program like Balena Etcher
  Restart your computer, enter the BIOS, and disable secure boot
  Boot the USB thumb drive with the rescue system on it. You will see the Login prompt, enter "root" there is no password so you will get a root shell prompt.
  Enter the command: sedutil-cli --scan 
      Expected Output: will show drive path, opal type and drive name
  Enter the following command to query a specific drive: sedutil-cli --query {drive} 
